properties.name: Colegio de Sta. Rosa Makati
properties.description: Posted by Talklat   A Level II PAASCU Accredited school, CSR boasts of morally upright, intellectually competent, and service oriented Filipinos who are pro-life, pro-family, pro-nation, and pro-God. Colegio de Sta. Rosa Makati is an exclusive all-girls Catholic school conveniently situated along Estrella Street. The school is near residential areas like Palm Village, Bel-Air, San Miguel Village, Cembo, Pinagkaisahan, and Guadalupe Viejo. It is also near Rockwell Complex, The Power Plant Mall, and Metro Club. CSR\'s facilities include a 750-seater auditorium, fully-equipped home economics laboratory, airconditioned classrooms with computer, projector, and plasma TV, grade school and high school libraries, prayer room, chapel, covered court, cafeteria, playground, indoor playroom, sewing room, typing room, grade school and high school computer laboratories, grade school and high school science laboratories, infirmary and dental clinic, and security systems (ID barcode scanners, CCTV cameras, security personnels, etc). CSR caters to students from Kindergarten 1 (Nursery) to High School 4 (4th Year). CSR rocks.

properties.name: Kenneth's Catering
properties.description: Posted by Talklat Kenneth\'s (inside NISMED) is okay. :P For about 70-80pesos, one can have a full meal complete with rice, viand, soup, and drink. The place isn\'t as crowded and noisy as the other canteens in the campus and it\'s airconditioned.

properties.name: Kha's Persian Food
properties.description: Posted by Talklat Satisfy your Persian cravings here at Kha\'s for very affordable meals. :D For about 85pesos, get a steak kabab to feed to your hungry stomach. :B

properties.name: Long Island
properties.description: Posted by Talklat Long Island sells pasta combo meals for about 80-100 pesos. Yummy enough for its price.

properties.name: Lutong Bahay
properties.description: Posted by Talklat This is the ultimate UP homestyle carinderia. For 50pesos a regular meal (rice, soup, viand) enjoy the company of your friends while lounging in the sala and watching local TV. Feel at home! I love their liempo.

properties.name: Mang Larry's Isawan
properties.description: Posted by Talklat Every afternoon, munch on some isaw, barbecue, and other smokin\' street foods at Mang Larry\'s famous isawan. But be there early or be prepared to wait in line. :P

properties.name: Mommy's Cantunan
properties.description: Posted by Talklat Mommy (the friendly fat lady managing the stall) sells what the common stalls in the campus usually sells - pancit canton, fish balls, squid balls, kwek kwek, hamburgers, sandwiches, hotdogs (and hotdog sandwiches), drinks, chips, and other snacks. For 25pesos, one can enjoy a pack of pancit canton of your choice and an order (1 stick) of fishballs. Good enough for a stomach in a rush. And there are many other combos to choose from! :D

properties.name: Power Plant Mall
properties.description: Posted by Talklat    Conveniently tucked away in the verdant "city within a city" that is the Rockwell Center, Power Plant Mall provides a unique and leisurely experience for the discerning shopper. Its four-level complex incorporates a mix of specialty brands, both international and local, a supermarket, lifestyle retailers, signature mini-anchors, themed restaurants and state-of-the-art cinemas. Power Plant Mall. Where Fashionable Manila shops.

properties.name: Short Island
properties.description: Posted by Talklat Short Island is the line of stores on the other side of the University Library where food are much cheaper than those in the other side (Long Island). They sell pretty much what the stalls sell only with more options (for chips, drinks, etc.). And you can get cellphone autoload services here as well. :))

properties.name: Tomato Bomb
properties.description: Posted by Talklat     Established June 2008, TOMATO BOMB! HQ came into the food business along Katipunan Avenue serving delightfully filling burgers, mouth-watering pasta, scrumptious rice meals and satisfying beverages. The stint was cut short as the area we were nested on had to be improved by local government. The search for another location did not come by easily nor quickly. Eventually, though, we were provided with partners and a better home in which we may continue the experience. To those who missed us, we missed you, too! Tomato Bomb HQ has a lot in store for you, especially during weekends where we feature jam sessions starting Fridays with the Sugar Hiccup band and the KONTRALUZ band during Saturdays. On the second Saturdays of every month, the ACTORS\' PLEYGRAWND perform various theatrical pieces ranging from vignettes of day-today life, poetry, music, inner dance, arnis and many other acts. You should not miss all these! We are open from 10 AM to 2 AM of the next day. TOMATO CLUB!!
